The paper deals with spectrum sensing in cognitive radio networks, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The proposed method involves analyzing the cyclic covariance matrix of received signals, which is a signal processing technique (cs.SP). The paper also discusses the detection performance in a fading channel, which is a system-level consideration (cs.SY). Finally, the paper is specifically focused on cognitive radio networks, which falls under the category of communications and networking (cs.CR).
